divs: sighting detailshi, one of the members of our photography group was taking lens testing pictures of san francisco from across the bay. he reported getting pictures of the train that goes down embarcadero. only there is no train that goes down embarcadero in sf. we have taken a look at his images and can't figure out what it is. can you guys please have a look and tell us? the thread on our user group is here. http:\\www.soocool.com\forum\viewtopic.php?t=2325 and his shot sequence is here: http:\\sis24.berkeley.edu\view\images\train2-animate.gif larger individual images are here: http:\\sis24.berkeley.edu\view\images\1024\ as you guys have a lot of experience explaining this stuff, please help us figure it out. thanks in advance, robert (robin) bourbonnais
